ğŸ¯ Business Objectives

The dashboard is designed to:

Analyze overall sales performance

Identify high-performing and underperforming product categories

Understand regional demand patterns (Tier 1 / Tier 2 / Tier 3)

Evaluate outlet type contribution

Support inventory planning and revenue optimization

ğŸ“Š Key KPIs & Metrics

The dashboard tracks the following metrics:

Total Sales

Category-wise Sales Performance

Sales by Outlet Location Type (Tier-wise)

Sales Contribution by Outlet Type

Average Sales per Item (Sales Efficiency)

Average Item Rating

Average Item Weight

Distinct Item Types & Distinct Items

Each KPI is aligned with a specific business question to ensure relevance and clarity.

ğŸ“ˆ Dashboard Pages & Insights
ğŸ”¹ Page 1: Sales Overview & Category Performance

Focuses on high-level business performance:

Top revenue-generating categories

Sales distribution across outlet location tiers

Sales efficiency analysis (average sales per item)

Executive KPI snapshot

Insights Delivered:

Revenue concentration across categories

Regional demand behavior

Performance comparison beyond sales volume

ğŸ”¹ Page 2: Outlet & Product Analysis

Focuses on operational and product-level insights:

Outlet type contribution analysis

Product mix analysis using ratings and attributes

Store format performance comparison

Insights Delivered:

Store format effectiveness

Product preference trends

Opportunities for inventory and outlet optimization

ğŸ§  Analytics Approach

This project follows a structured analytics workflow:

Define the business question â†’ choose the right KPIs â†’ design visuals that support decisions

Each visual is intentionally designed to answer a clear operational or business question, ensuring the dashboard remains intuitive and actionable.

